content:
Good afternoon,

I signed up for the 4pm Phone Bank, and ran into the following ZOOM login message/error on multiple devices, two different computers and iphone, over about a 30 minute period of checking from around 3:45 to 4:15pm.

"The host requires authentication on commercial Zoom platform to join this meeting. Please sign in with a commercial zoom account to join."

Will sign up for more phone banks in the future, but wanted to share in case any other callers run into this issue.
HI, sorry for your problem.  You need to create a Zoom Workplace profile and sign in to it to get to our zoom phone bank meeting
HI, sorry for your problem.  You need to create a Zoom Workplace profile and sign in to it to get to our zoom phone bank meeting
There is a way to create a free account, so you don’t need to sign up for a paid account.
yes there is an option for a free account, it should offer that
I was just in the zoom session, completed my shift was asked to join a breakout debrief room ans now nothing.

Im sorry <@1278039047184322710> , the breakout room for debriefs is a new procedure we are trying out so everyone can debrief and no one has to get skipped out on. Please bare with us as we also try and get used to this new format. We just want to make sure everyone feels heard and not skipped out on!
